        <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
            <t:creation/>
            <t:abstract>
                <t:p>A miniature showhing Jesus in majesty, typically enthroned and placed in a mandorla, surrounded by the Four Beasts. The image symbolizes the Second Coming 
                    and is inspired by Old and New Testament passages (e.g. Isaiah 6:1-3; Ezekiel 1:5-10; Revelation 4:6-9). A variant, known as Ancient of Days and influenced by passages such as Daniel 7:9, 
                    shows Christ represented as God the Father.
                </t:p>
            </t:abstract>
